history.content:
Please see the enrollment priorities here: https://eecs.berkeley.edu/resources/undergrads/eecs/degree-reqs/enrollment-policy. Mostly new students are prioritized.

If there are no seats in your category, you will be waitlisted. If there are seats in your category, but you choose full secondary sections, you will be waitlisted. If you have a time conflict, see the pinned post @3869.

I've added an open EE16A section to my shopping cart. If I enroll in it tomorrow, will I still be waitlisted due to reserved seats? If so, how would I get into the class? Or will I be able to enroll because the seats are open? I'm just very confused as to how i, as an incoming sophomore, can get only this class. Can anyone get into it without being waitlisted?
